place.name: CHILTHORNE DOMER
place.gazetteerText: CHILTHORNE-DOMER, a parish in Yeovil district, Somerset; near the Yeovil and Durston railway, 3¼ miles NW of Yeovil. Post town, Ilchester, under Taunton. Acres, 1, 392. Real property, £2, 658. Pop., 242. Houses, 52. The property is divided among a few. The living is a vicarage in the diocese of Bath and Wells. Value, £235.* Patron, the Rev. J. Baily. The church was repaired in 1861. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
